---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Repl from '../../../../components/Repl';
import SchemeRepl from '../../../../components/SchemeRepl';
import Neighbors from "../../../../components/Neighbors.astro";
import PrevNext from "../../../../components/PrevNext.astro";
---

<Layout title="Judson Ch.6 — Rings" favicon="🔗">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/abstract-algebra/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to algebra</a>

    <h1>Rings</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Tom Judson &middot; GFDL &middot; <a href="http://abstract.ups.edu/">Abstract Algebra: Theory and Applications, Ch. 6</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>ring</strong> is a set with two operations: addition (which forms an abelian group) and multiplication (which is associative and distributes over addition). Rings generalize the integers. <strong>Ideals</strong> are to rings what normal subgroups are to groups.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Definition -->
    <h3>Two operations</h3>
    <p>A ring (R, +, *) satisfies: (1) (R, +) is an abelian group with identity 0; (2) multiplication is associative: a*(b*c) = (a*b)*c; (3) distributive laws: a*(b+c) = a*b + a*c and (a+b)*c = a*c + b*c. Multiplication need not be commutative, and multiplicative inverses may not exist.</p>

    <!-- SVG: integers under + and x -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 360 160" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Ring Z -->
        <ellipse cx="180" cy="80" rx="160" ry="65" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <text x="180" y="15" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="13" fill-opacity="0.6">Z (the integers)</text>

        <!-- Addition side -->
        <text x="80" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="11">abelian group</text>
        <text x="80" y="75" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="20">+</text>
        <text x="80" y="95" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.6">identity: 0</text>
        <text x="80" y="110" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.6">inverse: -a</text>

        <!-- Multiplication side -->
        <text x="280" y="55" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="11">associative</text>
        <text x="280" y="75" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="20">&times;</text>
        <text x="280" y="95" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.6">identity: 1</text>
        <text x="280" y="110" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.6">no inverses (2 has none)</text>

        <!-- Distributive bridge -->
        <line x1="120" y1="80" x2="240" y2="80" stroke="#a78bfa" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="180" y="75" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a78bfa" font-size="10">distributes</text>

        <!-- Caption -->
        <text x="180" y="152" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="9" fill-opacity="0.3">Z is a ring: abelian group under +, associative under &times;, with distribution</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Z6 as a ring: addition mod 6, multiplication mod 6

(define (add a b) (modulo (+ a b) 6))
(define (mul a b) (modulo (* a b) 6))

; Distributive law: a * (b + c) = a*b + a*c
(define a 3) (define b 4) (define c 5)

(display "a*(b+c) = ") (display (mul a (add b c))) (newline)
(display "a*b+a*c = ") (display (add (mul a b) (mul a c))) (newline)

; Check: 3*(4+5 mod 6) = 3*3 mod 6 = 9 mod 6 = 3
;        3*4+3*5 mod 6 = 12+15 mod 6 = 0+3 mod 6 = 3
(display "Equal? ") (display (= (mul a (add b c))
                                (add (mul a b) (mul a c))))
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Z6 as a ring
add = lambda a, b: (a + b) % 6
mul = lambda a, b: (a * b) % 6

a, b, c = 3, 4, 5
lhs = mul(a, add(b, c))
rhs = add(mul(a, b), mul(a, c))
print("a*(b+c) = " + str(lhs))
print("a*b+a*c = " + str(rhs))
print("Distributive: " + str(lhs == rhs))
`} />
    </div>


    <!-- 2. Ideals -->
    <h3>Ideals</h3>
    <p>An <strong>ideal</strong> I of a ring R is a subring that absorbs multiplication: for any r in R and a in I, both r*a and a*r are in I. Ideals let you build <strong>quotient rings</strong> R/I, just as normal subgroups let you build quotient groups.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; In Z, the even numbers form an ideal.
; For any integer r and even number a, r*a is even.

(define (even? n) (= 0 (modulo n 2)))

; Check absorption: r * a is in ideal for various r, a
(display "Ideal test (multiples of 2 in Z):") (newline)
(let loop ((r -3))
  (when (<= r 3)
    (let ((a 4))  ; a is in ideal (even)
      (display "  ") (display r) (display " * ") (display a)
      (display " = ") (display (* r a))
      (display (if (even? (* r a)) " (even)" " ERROR"))
      (newline))
    (loop (+ r 1))))
; Z/2Z = (even, odd) is the quotient ring.
; It is isomorphic to Z2.
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Even integers form an ideal of Z
a = 4  # element of the ideal
for r in range(-3, 4):
    product = r * a
    print(str(r) + " * " + str(a) + " = " + str(product).rjust(3) + "  in ideal: " + str(product % 2 == 0))
`} />
    </div>


    <!-- 3. Ring homomorphisms -->
    <h3>Ring homomorphisms</h3>
    <p>A <strong>ring homomorphism</strong> f: R &rarr; S preserves both operations: f(a+b) = f(a)+f(b) and f(a*b) = f(a)*f(b). The kernel is an ideal, not just a subgroup.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Ring homomorphism: f: Z -> Z6, f(n) = n mod 6
; Preserves both + and *

(define (f n) (modulo n 6))

(define a 8) (define b 15)

(display "f(a+b) = ") (display (f (+ a b)))
(display "  f(a)+f(b) mod 6 = ") (display (modulo (+ (f a) (f b)) 6)) (newline)

(display "f(a*b) = ") (display (f (* a b)))
(display "  f(a)*f(b) mod 6 = ") (display (modulo (* (f a) (f b)) 6)) (newline)

; Kernel = multiples of 6 = ideal 6Z
(display "Kernel: multiples of 6")
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Ring homomorphism: Z -> Z6, f(n) = n mod 6
f = lambda n: n % 6
a, b = 8, 15

lhs_add = f(a + b)
rhs_add = (f(a) + f(b)) % 6
print("f(a+b) = " + str(lhs_add) + "  f(a)+f(b) mod 6 = " + str(rhs_add))

lhs_mul = f(a * b)
rhs_mul = (f(a) * f(b)) % 6
print("f(a*b) = " + str(lhs_mul) + "  f(a)*f(b) mod 6 = " + str(rhs_mul))

print("Kernel: multiples of 6")
`} />
    </div>


